OL,5,Cwalk out
OL,7,FNHS workers on Teesside have begun a
OL,8,Fthree-day strike in a row over pay.
OL,10,FMore than 1,000 healthcare assistants
OL,11,Fat North Tees & Hartlepool and South
OL,12,FTees Hospitals NHS Foundation Trusts
OL,13,Fwill walk out for 72 hours from Monday
OL,14,F8 April.
OL,16,FUnison, the union which represents the
OL,17,Fworkers, say they are calling for
OL,18,Fbetter pay to reflect the work they
OL,19,Fhave been doing.
